de.jannlab.data

Class SampleTools

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.jannlab.data.SampleTools

  • public class SampleTools
extends Object
    This class provides some useful methods for handling Samples and SampleSets. These concern normalizing features using mean and standard deviation or reading and writing comma-seperated-value (csv) files

    Author:
    Sebastian Otte
    See Also:
    Sample, SampleSet

    • Method Detail

      • mean

        public static double[] mean(SampleSet set)
        Computes the mean of a features for a given set of Samples. This method requires all Sample instances to have the same input size. The result is a double array with length of the input size containing the means for all features.

        Parameters:
        set - A set of Samples with the same input size.
        Returns:
        The mean values for all features.

      • stdDeviation

        public static double[] stdDeviation(SampleSet set,
                    double[] mean)
        Computes the standard deviation of all features for a given set of Samples based on an additionally given array of means. This method requires all Sample instances to have the same input size, which must also fit the length of the array of means. The result is a double array with length of the input size containing the standard derivations for all features.

        Parameters:
        set - A set of Samples with the same input size.
        mean - A previously computed array of means with length of input size.
        Returns:
        The standard derivations for all features.

      • normalize

        public static void normalize(SampleSet set,
             int... idxs)
        Normalized all features determined by a list of indices of a set of samples. The method computes the mean and the standard deviation first, which are both used for the normalization. It requires the samples to have the same input size.

        Parameters:
        set - The set of samples with the same input size.
        idxs - A given list of indices determining the feature which are to be normalized.

      • normalize

        public static void normalize(SampleSet set,
             double[] mean,
             double[] stddev,
             int... idxs)
        Normalizes all features determined by a list of indices of a set of samples. The normalization is based the given means and standard deviations. The method requires the samples to have the same input size which must also fit the length of the array of means and the array of standard deviations.

        Parameters:
        set - The set of samples with the same input size.
        idxs - A given list of indices determining the feature which are to be normalized.
